Tell us exactly how you'd like to pay

A fixed period, fixed cost finance plan linked or secured to the purchase of a vehicle. Pay a deposit and agree your annual mileage to calculate your monthly repayments. Pay your monthly repayments based on the remaining balance (plus interests). Upon final monthly repayment, you will automatically become the legal owner of the vehicle.

Lease purchase is a form of conditional sale agreement, which means that the regular payments are similar to a lease/rental agreement but you will own the car at the end of the deal. You may be asked to pay a deposit at the start of your agreement and a sum is usually deferred to the end of the deal. The deferred sum will be determined by the age and mileage of the car at the end of the agreement and must be paid to take ownership of the vehicle.

A fixed period, fixed cost finance plan linked or secured to the purchase of a vehicle. Pay a deposit, agree your annual mileage and repayment term to calculate your monthly repayments. Pay your monthly repayments based on the remaining balance (plus interests). At the end of the term, you will have two options: become the legal owner by paying the Option to Purchase fee or hand the vehicle back and make no further monthly payments, subject to mileage/vehicle condition.

A flexible finance plan with lower monthly repayments, shorter terms and a Guaranteed Minimum Future Value (GMFV or Optional Final Payment). Pay an initial deposit, agree your annual mileage allowance and repayment term to receive your GMFV. This is deducted with your deposit from the price of the vehicle. Pay your monthly repayments based on the remaining balance (plus interests). At the end of the term, you will have three options: ​become the legal owner by paying the GMFV and any fees. Hand the vehicle back and make no further monthly payments, subject to mileage/vehicle condition. Start a new PCP contract by part-exchanging your current vehicle for a new one.
Pay a deposit and a monthly rental

A form of finance with a single, larger up-front deposit and no monthly repayments. Agree your annual mileage and repayment term to receive your Guaranteed Minimum Future Value (GMFV/ Optional Final Payment). This is deducted with your deposit from the price of the vehicle. Pay the remaining balance (plus interests) as a single up-front payment. At the end of the term, you will have three options: ​become the legal owner by paying the GMFV and any fees. Hand the vehicle back and make no further monthly payments, subject to mileage/vehicle condition. Start a new PCP contract by part-exchanging your current vehicle for a new one.

A flexible form of leasing to fund the use of a vehicle. Agree on an annual mileage allowance over a fixed repayment term, make an advanced rental payment and use the vehicle while paying fixed monthly rental payments. At the end of the term, make no further monthly payments, subject to mileage/vehicle condition, and hand the vehicle back. Servicing plans, maintenance plans and road tax can be incorporated into the monthly repayments.

Financing a car with cash means you are paying for the vehicle in full via the retailer’s payment gateway, card or bank transfer facilities. You will own the car in full when payment is made and no further repayments will be required.
